# Given Positive integers nâ‰¤40 and kâ‰¤5. And return: The total number of rabbit pairs that will be present after n months, if we begin with 1 pair and in each generation, every pair of reproduction-age rabbits produces a litter of k rabbit pairs (instead of only 1 pair).

n = int(input('n = '))
k = int(input('k = '))

numlist = [0, 1]

for i in range(0,n-1):
    numlist.append(k*numlist[i]+numlist[i+1])
print(numlist[n])
